	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So I'm starting to get into SNESDev, and I was just wondering, what emulator should I use? I'd like to be able to view the pallete like you do in most NES emulators. I'd actually like an emulator that's pretty much like FCEUXD, but for SNES. What I have now is Geiger's Snes9x debugger for Windows, but I don't know if this is the best thing. When I go to dump the pallete, it shows me some hex values that make no sense to me. What is a good emulator to use for SNESDev?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
