	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, you both are right. SNES dev is kind of dead, maybe not totally dead but sure not as alive as NESdev. On the other hand, it's sure much harder to get a SNES game looking good with title such as Chrono Trigger or Stat Ocean out as compared with the NES where the best titles are impressive, but not THAT much impressive anymore. I don't see the point in doing SNESdev if you make NES looking games on the SNES.
<br />However, the GBAdev communauty is sure alive and the GBA has similar capabilities than those of the SNES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
