	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I would consider doing GBADev, but I really like the SNES a lot more for some reason. I hate the sound quality of GBA. When I play SNES ports on the GBA, I just think the sound was so much better on the SNES. I own Final Fantasy V on GBA and on SFC. The SFC version's sound was a lot more clear, and I enjoyed playing it more on the console. I don't know, I just am attracted to the SNES for some reason. I really do like NESDev, because it's not nearly as complicated as SNESDev, and I don't feel like I need a team of 30 developers to do everything for me so I can get something done in under 3 years.
<br />
<br />Graphically speaking, the SNES is great compared to the NES. Making a game look good isn't that hard if you have your good old buddy the scanner. I even use it for some things in my NES games, such as the portrait for a character. I painted it, scanned it, and Nintendoized it. I don't think I would have had the patience to make that portrait in a graphics editor such as YY-CHR. So yeah, a scanner is the way to go for me.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


